ueness must be enforced across requests and reflected in queue writes. Unit may miss duplicate detection at storage boundary. Integration-brake: no real OS/network/subprocess required; no AI dependency; no multi-agent chain. Rejected System because behavior text is storage state consistency, not OS/network effects.","test_description":"Use handler with real dedupe store/queue modules against local test DB/filesystem. Send same event ID twice. Assert first request writes once, second request does not create a second queued record.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When queue is full, return 503 and include `Retry-After`.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is error-contract mapping between queue module (capacity/full signal) and HTTP layer (status/header translation). Unit is too low if mapping can break across module boundary. Integration-brake: no real OS/network/subprocess required; no AI output; no multi-step agentic flow. Rejected System because behavior text is deterministic contract translation, not real network behavior.","test_description":"Run handler in-process with queue module configured to report/full-fail. Submit event and assert HTTP 503 plus `Retry-After` header value per policy; assert no successful enqueue side effect.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Persistent queue enforces configured capacity and rejects overflow events.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This targets interaction of queue logic with persistent storage accounting (count/size tracking + write rejection). A pure unit fake can miss storage-coupled limit bugs. Integration-brake: no required real external network/subprocess; no AI dependency; no